We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. Elevated levels of ACTH can lead to excess cortisol production, which can cause thinning of the skin, easy bruising, and bone loss, leading to an increased risk of pathologic fractures. Weight loss and hypoglycemia are not commonly associated with ACTH-secreting pituitary adenomas. Eosinophilia may be seen in some infections or allergic reactions, but is not directly related to an ACTH-secreting pituitary adenoma.
